<br>
I saw a lot of bards asking for an upgrade to 55 bellow or dirge, which we didn't get.  Or a mana based DD nuke that was somewhat substantial.  We didn't get that either.  It would be nice to have something where every hour or so we can go &quot;wow neat&quot;, or something we can drop on a raid mob that wouldn't be huge but would at least be something (dirge sucks because of the AE effect and it doesn't land that hard for a lvl 70 and uses too much mana to be that useful, and 55 bellow gets resisted so much its barely worth using up a song slot).  I guess I just don't understand why BL's would get considered for this but not bards, especially when they have some halfway decent nukes already (not saying take it away, its overpowered, just that it would be nice to have a similar ability).<br>
<br>
A lot of bards also really wanted an offensive type discipline or at least an AA activated DPS ability so we could do SOMETHING when offensive was called, or something to do while grouping.  I understood when we didn't have one before, because we didn't have double attack, and only offensive discs go to dps classes.  Well they gave it to beastlords.  And this isn't to say they should take it away, because I think its a great disc for them to have.  I just don't understand the reasoning behind them getting one and we don't.  They also got an activated AA ability (some sort of kick ability) and while that isn't a huge DPS increase, its at least something fun they can do every now and then that can crit for a nice amount.  Why is something along those lines too much to ask for?  They're not a melee dps class and neither are we, but they get some nifty toys?  <br>
<br>
beastlords:  GoD kick aa, OoW nuke AA, offensive disc<br>
<br>
bards:  bellow aa (woo!), and AE ramp?   <br>
<br>
wtf?<br>
<br>
<br>
and once again, i'm not saying &quot;nerf BL's&quot; or that they shouldn't have these abilities.  I'm just saying... whats the reasoning behind them getting these things and we don't? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=suladasbardspeed>Suladas Bardspeed</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 373<br> <font color=#330000>(8/20/04 6:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19697.topic&index=82>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Master of Disgust</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Bards get Infuriate (AE ramp with our paltry DPS), which makes no sense due to massive mob DPS. Any time I have more than one mob in camp, it will be mezzed, not tickled by my EoE. Only useful in AE encounters, where it wont matter anyways. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
